benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/simplePlan - Add a simple plan entry in the current version of the catalog

covered: POST Valid Payload: Valid plan creation with required fields (TC01) and optional headers (TC02).
POST Invalid Payload: 400 responses for missing headers (TC03), missing fields (TC04), invalid currency (TC05), empty body (TC08), malformed JSON (TC09), and invalid input patterns (TC18).
POST Duplicate Submission: Duplicate planId handling (TC06).
POST Large Payloads: Handling very large payloads (TC15).
POST Validation: Validation of field constraints (TC12, TC13, TC04, TC05, TC18).
POST Server Error Handling: Service unavailable (TC11) and integration degradations/network issues (TC16, TC24).
405 Method Not Allowed: Unsupported HTTP method test (TC14).
Integration with dependent services: Dependent catalog services integration (TC23, TC24).
Backward compatibility: Tests for previous API versions (TC21).
Optional headers support: Validations for optional header usage (TC02).
gaps: GET Method: No tests cover GET specific behaviors (Valid Request, Empty Response, Pagination, Query Parameters, Caching, Rate Limiting).
PUT Method: No tests for update semantics or concurrency in updates.
PATCH Method: No tests for patch semantics.
DELETE Method: No tests for delete semantics.
Rate Limiting: Not tested (no tests for throttling or burst handling).
Internal Server Errors: No tests for 500 Internal Server Error, only 503 in some cases.
recommendations: Add GET tests to verify retrieval of created plan and other list behaviors.
Add PUT/PATCH/DELETE tests to cover update and removal flows of catalog plans.
Add rate-limiting tests to verify throttling and bursts.
Add caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control behavior.
Add tests for 500 Internal Server Error scenarios and error recovery.
Add tests for 403 Forbidden responses to complement 401 Unauthorized.
Validate consistent 201 responses including Location / URI header for created plan.
